@startuml seq-06-password-change
' ============================================================
' SEQ-06: POST /auth/change-password
' Scope : Contract 05B §5B.3 change flow.
' Key  : On success, revoke ALL refresh tokens for the user —
'        every other open session is forced back to /login.
'        Password policy is enforced in IAuthService, not the DTO.
' ============================================================

title SEQ-06: POST /auth/change-password — revoke all sessions

autonumber

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11

skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #2E7D32
  LifeLineBorderColor #1B5E20
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #E8F5E9
  ParticipantBorderColor #1B5E20
  ActorBackgroundColor #FFEFCD
  ActorBorderColor #AA6622
  NoteBackgroundColor #FFFDE7
  NoteBorderColor #AA8800
}

actor "Dashboard" as Dashboard
participant "JwtBearer" as JWT
participant "IActorContext" as Actor
participant "AuthEndpoints\n.MapPost(/auth/change-password)\n[RequireAuthorization]" as AE
participant "AuthService" as Auth
participant "IUserRepository" as Users
participant "IRefreshTokenRepository" as RT
participant "IPasswordHasher" as Hasher
participant "IClock" as Clock
participant "AuditService" as Audit
database  "controlit_users" as UDB
database  "controlit_refresh_tokens" as RTDB
database  "controlit_audit_log" as ADB

== 1. Authenticated request ==

Dashboard -> JWT: POST /auth/change-password\nAuthorization: Bearer <access>\n{ currentPassword, newPassword }
activate JWT
JWT -> JWT: validate HS256, exp
JWT -> Actor: populate ClaimsPrincipal (user_id)
JWT -> AE: authenticated
deactivate JWT
activate AE

AE -> Auth: ChangePasswordAsync(\n  user_id=Actor.UserId, req)
activate Auth

== 2. Verify current password ==

Auth -> Users: GetByIdAsync(user_id)
Users -> UDB: SELECT *
UDB --> Users
Users --> Auth

Auth -> Hasher: Verify(req.CurrentPassword, user.PasswordHash)
Hasher --> Auth: bool

alt current password wrong
  Auth -> Audit: Record(AUTH_PASSWORD_CHANGE_FAILURE,\n  user_id, reason="bad current")
  Audit -> ADB: INSERT (no password fields ever logged)
  Auth --> AE: UnauthorizedException
  AE --> Dashboard: 401 Unauthorized
end

== 3. Password policy (enforced here, not in DTO) ==

Auth -> Auth: EnforcePolicy(req.NewPassword):\n  length >= 12 AND\n  has_upper + has_lower + has_digit + has_symbol >= 3

alt policy fails
  Auth --> AE: ValidationException(reasons)
  AE --> Dashboard: 400 Bad Request\n{ errors: [...] }
  note right of Auth
    See test PasswordPolicy_RejectsUnder12Chars_And_LowComplexity.
    Reasons are specific ("needs 12+ chars", "needs 3 of 4 classes")
    because the caller is already authenticated — no enumeration risk.
  end note
end

== 4. Reject reuse ==

Auth -> Hasher: Verify(req.NewPassword, user.PasswordHash)
Hasher --> Auth: bool

alt new == current
  Auth --> AE: ValidationException("must differ from current")
  AE --> Dashboard: 400 Bad Request
end

== 5. Hash + persist + clear flags ==

Auth -> Hasher: Hash(req.NewPassword)   // bcrypt wf=12
Hasher --> Auth: newHash

Auth -> Clock: UtcNow
Auth -> Users: UpdateAsync(user with:\n  password_hash=newHash,\n  password_changed_at=now,\n  must_change_password=false,\n  failed_login_count=0,\n  locked_until=null)
Users -> UDB: UPDATE
UDB --> Users
Users --> Auth

== 6. Revoke ALL refresh tokens for the user ==

Auth -> RT: RevokeAllForUserAsync(user_id)
RT -> RTDB: UPDATE controlit_refresh_tokens\n  SET revoked_at = now\n  WHERE user_id = @uid\n    AND revoked_at IS NULL
RTDB --> RT
RT --> Auth

note right of Auth
  Every other open session across every device is now
  invalidated. Their next /auth/refresh returns 401 and
  the client redirects to /login. The CURRENT session's
  access token is still valid until it naturally expires
  (<=15 min), but the caller is about to be forced out
  too — see step 7.
  Verified by test ChangePassword_RevokesAllRefreshTokensForUser.
end note

Auth -> Audit: Record(AUTH_PASSWORD_CHANGE, user_id, ip, ua)
Audit -> ADB: INSERT
ADB --> Audit

Auth --> AE: ok
deactivate Auth

== 7. Response — client-side forced re-login ==

AE -> AE: clear Set-Cookie: refresh_token=; Max-Age=0
AE --> Dashboard: 204 No Content
deactivate AE

note right of Dashboard
  Dashboard:
  - drops in-memory access token
  - navigates to /login with a "password changed, please re-login"
    toast
  - next action will trigger /auth/login → new access + refresh pair
end note

@enduml
